Food Grade Taurine is an organic amino‑sulfonic acid widely used as a nutritional supplement in energy drinks, health‑care products, pet food and fortified beverages. It plays a supportive role in cardiovascular health, neurological development and metabolic regulation. Commercial production primarily follows two synthesis routes – the Ethylene Oxide Method and the Ethanol‑Amine Method – both delivering the high purity required for food‑grade applications.

